    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Plugin will allow you to fetch the WP REST API call with a &#8220;lang&#8221; variable.<br />\nIt will retrieve the right content from WPML.</p>\n<p>Tested with the latest version of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>WPML 3.2.7</li>\n<li>WP REST API 2.0-beta4</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<p>Install the plugin in your wp-content/plugins/ directory.<br />\nThen:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Make a call to &#8220;http://yoursite/wp-json/posts/?lang=it&#8221;</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>How I can fetch my custom post type in current language?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Add &#8216;suppress_filters&#8217; =&gt; false on get_posts/WP_Query call</p>\n<p>get_posts([<br />\n    &#8216;post_type&#8217; =&gt; &#8216;custom_post&#8217;,<br />\n    &#8216;suppress_filters&#8217; =&gt; false<br />\n]);</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
